Map Viewer Tools
 

When a tool is selected (click or tap) a dialogue box with options available will appear on screen



  Draw and Measure
The ‘Draw and Measure’ tool allows you to draw points or shapes on the map with options enabling you to adjust line thickness, colour, transparency or show measurements etc. 

Functionality is limited on mobile devices.





  Swipe
The Swipe Layer tool can be used to interactively reveal layers beneath the layer being swiped. This tool makes it easy to see what is underneath a particular layer without having to turn it off in the layer list. The layer you wish to swipe need to be turned on initially in the layer list.

  Bookmarks
The ‘Bookmarks’ tool allows you to store and name numerous locations to return to at a later date. 

  Print
The ‘Print’ tool allows you to print a map in a chosen format with options to adjust scale and layout.

  Information
The ‘Information’ tool provides information on the use of the map viewer

  Share
The ‘Share’ tool allows you to share the extent of the map you are currently viewing using a hyperlink, via social media or for embedding in a website using an iFrame. 

Layer List, Basemap Gallery & Legend
 

Layer List
Provides a list of available layers, with options to turn on/off, expand list, reorder, adjust transparency and links to further information about the data.

Basemap Gallery 
Provides a gallery of available basemaps to choose from.

Legend
Displays a legend for the current layers.


Show Map Overview

 
Displays an overview of the current location on the map.


Map Navigation Tools
 
Allows users to zoom in and out and revert to default view.

Popup Windows
To view additional information about active layers, click or tap on the area of interest on the map. A popup window will appear displaying descriptions, additional attributes, and hyperlinks. If you have more than one layer turned on, the information will be displayed in separate tabs.
